Add flake8 configuration

This configuration sets the maximum line length to 130
characters because some unit tests can have long lines;
excludes some directories from the analysis, such as build,
dist, etc; and ignores the next errors:

  * E129 visually indented line with same indent as next logical line
  * E402 module level import not at top of file
  * F841 local variable '_' is assigned to but never used

Add flake8 tests to TravisCI

This tool will check the code style of the code pushed
to the repository, failing the build if flake8 detects
any error.

[puppetforge] Apply archive to PuppetForge backend

This code allows the PuppetForge backend to store fetched data to
archives. Thus it allows to transparently play back previous fetch
executions, enabling the recovery of the stored data as it was
originally collected from the data source.

Add tests requirements pip file

By adding this file, it was necessary also to modify travis
configuration file to use `requirements_tests.txt` file
instead of installing each requirement individually.

Add support to run tests using setup.py file

To run user-defined commands using setup.py it is necessary
to add Command derivated classes. In this case, TestCommand
class was included to run tests.

The inclusion of `pkg_resources` is necessary to ensure that
Perceval is imported from the right path, inserting its location
in the first position of `sys.path` variable. This change is due
to the use of namespaces by Perceval.

To avoid import problems, it was necessary to add `base.py`
script, an empty `__init__.py` file into tests directory and
change how the package is imported in `test_puppetforge.py`.

Include metadata files and tests in sdist packages

Source distribution packages will start including
some missing metadata files such as the license and
the list of authors.

It also will include the code needed to test the
software. This is useful for distros which could
need to pass some tests before generating the packages
(e.g, in rpm or deb formats).

[travis] Upgrade setuptools and pip

This code upgrades the setuptools and pip. This change
stems from the fix at: chaoss/grimoirelab-perceval#643
It was needed to fix the CI tests that were failing due
to the following error:
```
File "../python3.5/site-packages/setuptools/sandbox.py", line 44, in _execfile
  code = compile(script, filename, 'exec')
File "/tmp/easy_install-wu9lgsxc/pandoc-2.0a4/setup.py", line 11
  error = f"pip is not installed, refer to <{url}> for instructions."
                                                                    ^
SyntaxError: invalid syntax
```
